<title>USA: Sterling Commerce adopts rights plan.</title>
<headline>Sterling Commerce adopts rights plan.</headline>
<dateline>DALLAS 1996-12-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sterling Commerce Inc said it has adopted a share purchase rights plan that provides for rights to be issued to stockholders of record on December 31.</p>
<p>The rights plan is intended to protect Sterling Commerce and its stockholders against potentially coercive takeover practices or takeover bids which are inconsistent with the interests of the company and its stockholders.</p>
<p>Under the plan, the rights will initally trade together with the common stock and will not be exercisable. The rights will become exercisable if a person or group acquires 15 percent or more of Sterling Commerce's outstanding shares.</p>
